@startuml
title Rithmomachia Turn Phase Transitions (v0.2 - with contextual rules)

skinparam state {
  BackgroundColor<<Automatic>> #E1F5FE
  BorderColor<<Automatic>> #01579B
}

[*] --> START

state START <<Automatic>>
note right of START
Entry point of a turn.
Always transitions automatically
to PRE_CAPTURE_COMPUTATION.
end note

START --> PRE_CAPTURE_COMPUTATION

state PRE_CAPTURE_COMPUTATION <<Automatic>>
note right of PRE_CAPTURE_COMPUTATION
PhaseResolver computes capture opportunities.
If none exist → skip to MOVE_COMPUTATION.
If exists → user must choose.
end note

PRE_CAPTURE_COMPUTATION --> PRE_CAPTURE_APPLICATION : if options exist
PRE_CAPTURE_COMPUTATION --> MOVE_COMPUTATION : else


state PRE_CAPTURE_APPLICATION {
    state "User Decision" as PCA_Choice <<choice>>
    [*] --> PCA_Choice
    PCA_Choice --> MOVE_COMPUTATION : PreCaptureAction applied
}

note right of PRE_CAPTURE_APPLICATION
User executes a capture BEFORE movement.
May modify board state and actor position.
end note


state MOVE_COMPUTATION <<Automatic>>

note right of MOVE_COMPUTATION
Core movement resolution phase.

Two variants exist:

1. Standard MOVE:
   - normal movement options

2. Extended MOVE (contextual rule):
   - activated if a capture occurred earlier in turn
   - allows reintroduction-related behavior
   - uses actorPos (PieceAtPosition)

IMPORTANT:
Reintroduction is NOT a phase.
It is a consequence of MOVE computation context.
end note

MOVE_COMPUTATION --> MOVE_APPLICATION


state MOVE_APPLICATION {
    state "User Decision" as MA_Choice <<choice>>
    [*] --> MA_Choice
    MA_Choice --> POST_CAPTURE_COMPUTATION : MoveAction applied
    MA_Choice --> END : irregular move
}

note right of MOVE_APPLICATION
Executes movement.
Produces landing position used by next phase.
end note


state POST_CAPTURE_COMPUTATION <<Automatic>>

note right of POST_CAPTURE_COMPUTATION
Post-move resolution phase.

Evaluates:
- capture opportunities
- follow-up interactions
- effects of reintroduced pieces

If options exist → player decision required.
Else → end of turn.
end note

POST_CAPTURE_COMPUTATION --> POST_CAPTURE_APPLICATION : if options exist
POST_CAPTURE_COMPUTATION --> END : else


state POST_CAPTURE_APPLICATION {
    state "User Decision" as PCA2_Choice <<choice>>
    [*] --> PCA2_Choice
    PCA2_Choice --> END : PostCaptureAction applied
}

note right of POST_CAPTURE_APPLICATION
Final interaction phase of the turn.
May trigger victory or further board changes.
end note


state END <<Automatic>>

note right of END
Turn cleanup phase.
Switch player and restart cycle.
end note

END --> START


state VICTORY_CHECK <<Automatic>>
note right of VICTORY_CHECK
Victory is checked after every mutation phase.
If victory condition met → WIN.
end note

state WIN
WIN --> [*]

state PAT
PAT --> [*]

@enduml